The paper deals with the problem of sparse recovery, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of adaptivity in solving this problem, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper presents an application in solving the problem of finding duplicates in a data stream, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
